{"author":{"id":"2604aaeeb96693406a0c3b08e5f5912b100fc414cdf8fa69d513f6ba851bf6cd"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1651060425,"nonce":"zLUCWa2jfLBg8xVPmNxx6xuNE2A=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOAW4Y0s5IjbGs","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/4527","origin":"github"},"title":"Functionality of MultiQC does not correspond to the stated version","message":"Hello!\nI see that [the current version of MultiQC provided by IUC in Galaxy Toolshed is 1.11](https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/commit/57b36cfbdd1663aef43d03b76e37364cc5bdeef3). According to MultiQC release data, support for inputs from the Kraken metagenomic classification tool [was introduced already in MultiQC v1.9](https://github.com/ewels/MultiQC/releases/tag/v1.9). However, neither in usegalaxy.eu, nor in any other Galaxy instance with a recent version of MultiQC (v1.9 or later) the tool supports inputs from Kraken (no option for Kraken in the drop-down menu when setting up a MultiQC analysis in Galaxy).\n\nWhy the functionality of MultiQC in Galaxy does not match the functionality of the corresponding version of a stand-alone MultiQC installation?","files":null}]}